sql:
SELECT type, COUNT(bicycle_id) AS count
FROM bicycles
GROUP BY type;

external_knowledge:
- "shining star" refers to the station with the highest performance in terms of profit and weather;
- "highest profit" is calculated by subtracting the total maintenance cost from the total revenue;
- "most favorable weather conditions" are determined by the average weather situation, with higher values indicating better weather.
